column1: #Text=How the Grand Gallipoot Joined The Nomes
#Text=After leaving the Whimsies , Guph continued on his journey and penetrated far into the Northwest .
#Text=He wanted to get to the Country of the Growleywogs , and in order to do that he must cross the Ripple Land , which was a hard thing to do .
#Text=For the Ripple Land was a succession of hills and valleys , all very steep and rocky , and they changed places constantly by rippling .
#Text=While Guph was climbing a hill it sank down under him and became a valley , and while he was descending into a valley it rose up and carried him to the top of a hill .
#Text=This was very perplexing to the traveler , and a stranger might have thought he could never cross the Ripple Land at all .

#Text=But Guph knew that if he kept steadily on he would get to the end at last ; so he paid no attention to the changing hills and valleys and plodded along as calmly as if walking upon the level ground .
#Text=The result of this wise persistence was that the General finally reached firmer soil and , after penetrating a dense forest , came to the Dominion of the Growleywogs .

#Text=No sooner had he crossed the border of this domain when two guards seized him and carried him before the Grand Gallipoot of the Growleywogs , who scowled upon him ferociously and asked him why he dared intrude upon his territory .
#Text=" I 'm the Lord High General of the Invincible Army of the Nomes , and my name is Guph , " was the reply .
#Text=" All the world trembles when that name is mentioned .

column1: #Text=The Gallipoot made a signal and at once his attendants picked up General Guph and carried him away to a prison , where the jailer amused himself by sticking pins in the round fat body of the old Nome , to see him jump and hear him yell .
